{"id":1096996549,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"4 days, 16 hours","timestamp":1699759934,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"175 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1096996549/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Minimum Operations to Maximize Last Elements in Arrays","memory":"16.7 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def minOperations(self, nums1, nums2):\n        ans1, ans2 = 0, 0\n\n        n = len(nums1)\n\n        # Check conditions for swapping in nums1\n        for i in range(n - 1):\n            if nums1[i] <= nums1[n - 1] and nums2[i] <= nums2[n - 1]:\n                continue\n            elif nums1[i] <= nums2[n - 1] and nums2[i] <= nums1[n - 1]:\n                ans1 += 1\n            else:\n                ans1 = float('inf')\n                break\n\n        ans2 = 1\n        nums1[n - 1], nums2[n - 1] = nums2[n - 1], nums1[n - 1]  # Swap last elements\n\n        # Check conditions for swapping in nums2\n        for i in range(n - 1):\n            if nums1[i] <= nums1[n - 1] and nums2[i] <= nums2[n - 1]:\n                continue\n            elif nums1[i] <= nums2[n - 1] and nums2[i] <= nums1[n - 1]:\n                ans2 += 1\n            else:\n                ans2 = float('inf')\n                break\n\n        ans = min(ans1, ans2)\n        if ans == float('inf'):\n            return -1\n        return ans\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"minimum-operations-to-maximize-last-elements-in-arrays","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
